<DESCRIPT>  ENTERTAINMENT; FESTIVAL; SOUTH-BAY; LIST  </DESCRIPT>
<LEADPARA>  From San Jose's huge Mexican Independence Day Parade to Pleasanton's Pasta
Festival, there's fun, food and entertainment to suit any taste this weekend.
Admission to all is free, though there are charges for food and other items.
Here are some of the highlights:; Fiestas Patrias  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Local  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  A FESTIVE WEEKEND  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>   Celebrates Mexico's independence; (box)Key events:  Parade, food, arts,
crafts, entertainment.; (box)Where:  Parade begins at Ninth and Santa Clara
streets in San Jose; other events at Almaden Boulevard and San Fernando
Street.; (box)When:  Parade begins at 10 a.m. Sunday; booths open at 10 a.m.
Sunday; entertainment at four stages 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. Sunday; art exhibit 6
to 10 a.m. Saturday and 10 a.m. to 5 p.m. Sunday at the Old Convention Center
at Park Avenue and Market Street.; Garin Apple Festival  (box)Key events: 
Cider tasting, old-fashioned games, square dancing, blacksmith demonstrations
and apple orchard tours.; (box)Where:  Garin Regional Park, Hayward.;
(box)When:  11 a.m. to 4 p.m. Sunday. Participants may bring homemade pies for
judging from 12:30 to 1:30 p.m.; Santa Clara Art; and Wine Festival  (box)Key
events:  Wines from Bay Area wineries, arts and crafts booths, foods, music,
games, and "Kids' Kingdom" with petting zoo, face painting and more.;
(box)Where:  Central Park, on Kiley Boulevard north of Homestead Road in Santa
Clara.; (box)When:  10 a.m. to 5 p.m. Saturday and Sunday.; Aki Matsuri 
(box)Key events:  Traditional Japanese-American outdoor festival, including
children's activities, costumed dancers, Taiko drummers, singers, food.;
(box)Where:  Wesley Methodist Church, 566 N. Fifth St., San Jose.; (box)When: 
Noon to 5 p.m. Saturday; American Indian Summer Festival  (box)Key events: 
Dancing, singing, food, crafts, fun run, Indian village contests.; (box)Where:
 Spartan Stadium, Seventh and Alma streets, San Jose.; (box)When:  Noon to 11
p.m. Saturday; noon to 6 p.m. Sunday.; Willow Glen; Founders' Day  (box)Key
events:  10K run, 5K walk, parade, food, arts and crafts, wine tasting,
entertainment. Run or walk costs $18.; (box)Where:  Lincoln Avenue between
Minnesota Avenue and Willow Street, San Jose.; (box)When:  Run begins at 8
a.m., walk at 8:15; other activities 9 a.m to 5 p.m. Sunday.; Almaden Art; and
Wine Festival  (box)Key events:  130 artists and artisans, wine- and
ale-tasting, entertainment.; (box)Where:  Parma Park, next to the Almaden
Community Center, 6445 Camden Ave. in San Jose.; (box)When:  10 a.m. to 6 p.m.
Sunday.; Newark Days  (box)Key events:  Parade featuring championship horses,
antique autos; food and game booths; pet contest.; (box)Where:  Parade starts
at City Hall on Newark Boulevard near Thornton Avenue and goes north to the
community center on Cedar Boulevard and Newark boulevards, where other events
will be.; (box)When:  Parade begins at 10 a.m. Saturday. Booths open noon to 5
p.m. Saturday and Sunday. Pet contest at 1:30 p.m. Sunday.; (box)Pleasanton
Pasta; Festival  (box)Key events:  Food, arts and crafts, beer and wine
garden, cooking demonstrations.; (box)Where:  Main Street, Pleasanton.;
(box)When:  10 a.m. to 6 p.m. Saturday, and 10 a.m. to 5 p.m. Sunday.; Mall
anniversary; Eastridge Mall's 20th anniversary; (box)Key events:  Hands-on
space and science exhibit sponsored by the Engineering Careers Council and
NASA.; (box)Where:  Eastridge Mall, on Tully Road west of Capitol Expressway
in San Jose.; (box)When:  10 a.m. to 5 p.m. Saturday and Sunday.; Trail
dedication; Dedication of Almaden Valley leg of Bay Area Ridge Trail; (box)Key
events:  Hiking, biking, horseback riding.; (box)Where:  Santa Teresa County
Park. For specific locations, call (408) 268-8220.; (box)When:  Events begin
at 9:30 a.m. Saturday; dedication ceremony at 12:30 p.m; barbecue at 1 p.m.  </TEXT>
